This completes the proof that `M ∆ P.edgeSet` is a matching. The key insight is that the symmetric difference of two matchings is a matching if the original matchings are disjoint. The proof uses the fact that the symmetric difference of two matchings can be seen as a new matching by considering the alternating path structure.
